Parliament, Wednesday, 20 February 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Arts and Culture will tomorrow deliberate on the 25 shortlisted candidates for the Pan South African Language Board (PanSALB). During the interviews to shortlist nominees for the board, which were held in November 2018, candidates were asked to a range of questions about language diversity, ethical leadership and maintaining the integrity in the board, among other things. The committee invites members of the media and the public to attend, in the interests of strengthening public participation and transparency. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Thursday, 21 February 2019
	Time: 08:00 
	Venue: Committee Room G26, National Assembly building. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ARTS AND CULTURE, MS XOLISWA TOM. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
